<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Myleene Klass flashed her eye-watering £35,000 black diamond ring as she headed to work at Global Studios on Friday. </p>

<p>The presenter, 42, passionately kissed her new fiancé Simon Motson goodbye as he dropped her off in London ahead of her Smooth Radio show. </p>

<p>Myleene looked effortlessly stylish in a plunging zebra print maxi dress, but all attention was drawn to her bespoke ring.  </p>

<p>Wow: Myleene Klass flashed her eye-watering £35,000 black diamond ring as she headed to work at Global Studios on Friday</p>

<p>Myleene teased a hint of cleavage in the summer dress which featured ruffles on the sleeves. </p>

<p>She added a boost to her height with velvet platform heels and accessorised the outfit with oversized shades and one of her many Chanel handbags.</p>

<p>The former HearSay star wore her brunette locks in soft waves and accentuated her flawless complexion with a pretty make-up look.  </p>

<p>Smitten: The presenter, 42, passionately kissed her new fiancé Simon Motson goodbye as he dropped her off in London ahead of her Smooth Radio show</p>

<p>Gorgeous: Myleene looked effortlessly stylish in a plunging zebra print maxi dress, but all attention was drawn to her bespoke ring</p>

<p>Wow: Myleene settled on a black diamond ring that is the only one of its kind</p>

<p>Earlier this week, Myleene revealed she designed her own engagement ring following the proposal.</p>

<p>The mother-of-three was astounded when her partner of five years popped the question last month with a promise ring on the fifth anniversary of their first date.</p>

<p>After the initial shock wore off, the couple got to work designing a unique band for the star, eventually settling on a black diamond ring that is the only one of its kind.</p>

<p>For the project, Myleene enlisted the help of Ira Kormind, the director of 77 Diamonds and a personal friend of hers.  </p>

<p>Romance: The media personality admitted she was shocked when her partner popped the question last month on the fifth anniversary of their first date</p>

<p>Together, they came up with a head-turning 7.63 carat emerald-cut natural black diamond centre stone and a dazzling split band set with 114 delicate white diamonds, meaning the whole ring comes in at around 9-carats in total. </p>

<p>Oliver Horner Gemologist Prestige Pawnbrokers of Channel 4's Posh Pawn told MailOnline that the ring would retail up to £35,000. </p>

<p>Speaking to Hello! magazine, Myleene told how Simon, 45, got down on one knee in their garden shed which he made into a replica of where they had their first date and surprised her with a nine-carat diamond ring. </p>

<p>Replica: Myleene told how Simon got down on one knee in the couple's garden shed, which he recreated into a replica of the place they had their first date</p>

<p>A night to remember: Ever the romantic, Myleene told how Simon also decorated the shed walls with framed photos and filled their garden with fairy lights </p>

<p>She said: 'We're engaged! I was absolutely blown away. He even replicated the dinner we had – burger and fries, followed by cherry pie.</p>

<p>'When he got down on one knee and started fumbling around under the table, I thought he was joking. Then I thought: 'Oh my God, he's for real.' I was completely speechless.' </p>

<p>The couple's engagement has delighted Myleene's daughters Ava, 13, and Hero, nine, who have been determined to see the couple walk down the aisle while Simon's children, a 13-year-old son and nine-year-old daughter, are also thrilled. </p>

<p>Myleene and Simon began dating in 2015 after she split from husband Graham Quinn in 2012, and they welcomed their first child together, son Apollo, in August last year. </p>

<p>Overjoyed: The couple's engagement has delighted Myleene's daughters Ava, 13, and Hero, nine, who have been determined to see the couple walk down the aisle  </p>
